The `emptyValue` attribute is not set in `CsvArgumentsProvider` -- it defaults to `null`.

We could configure the internal `CsvParserSettings` with `settings.setEmptyValue("");`. See https://github.com/uniVocity/univocity-parsers/blob/master/src/main/java/com/univocity/parsers/csv/CsvParserSettings.java#L70

@junit-team/junit-lambda Thoughts?
